# Terraform Cloud Backend Configuration Example
#
# Use this when you want managed state with HashiCorp Terraform Cloud
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. Create account at https://app.terraform.io
#   2. Create API token at https://app.terraform.io/app/settings/tokens
#   3. Run: terraform login (paste your API token when prompted)
#   4. Create organization in Terraform Cloud
#
# Benefits:
#   - Managed by HashiCorp
#   - Free tier available (state + runs + VCS integration)
#   - Web UI for state management
#   - Built-in team collaboration
#   - Run history and approvals

terraform {
  cloud {
    # Your organization name in Terraform Cloud
    organization = "my-org"
    
    workspaces {
      # Workspace name - use different ones for different environments
      name = "devops13-studio-dev"
    }
  }
}

# Usage:
# 1. Create account at https://app.terraform.io
# 2. Create organization (e.g., "my-org")
# 3. Run: terraform login (generates and stores API token)
# 4. Replace the backend block in main.tf with this one
# 5. Run: terraform init
# 6. Answer "yes" when prompted to migrate state
#
# Now all state is managed by Terraform Cloud!
# Check https://app.terraform.io/app/your-org/workspaces/ to see your state
